Focsani Tour Guide Attraction_icon Title Description
//Category Strings Must See Museums Parks Food
//Locations Strings Union Square The square surrounding the obelisk is situated on the old border between Tara Romaneasca and Moldova. Every year, on January 24th, the great act of the Union is celebrated. Municipal Theater "Maior Gheorghe Pastia" Inaugurated in 1913 features elements in the architecture of the theaters of Odessa and Berlin, as well as a good acoustics. The building is a historical monument, the interest falling on the interior dome, beautifully decorated. The Popular Athenaeum "Maior Gheorghe Pastia" It is an interwar building, a historical monument, linked to the personality of Major Pastia, the founder of the theater in the town of Milcov. The Mausoleum of the Heroes The Mausoleum of the Heroes in Focsani has three main graves, in the walls there are boxes with the bones of the unknown heroes fallen in the battles of 1918, the surroundings are arranged in a beautiful park. Church of Saint John the Baptist It was part of the entire monastery, dedicated to "The Birth of Saint John the Baptist", founded by Prince of Wallachia, Grigore Ghica, in 1661. Lordy Wine Cellar This historic monument dates from the 14th century, during the reign of Stephen the Great. In 1834, ruler Mihai Sturza, in possession of more than 200 hectares of vine, became the owner of the ruins of two stone cellars.
Vrancea Museum The Vrancea Museum has rich collections of archeological, ethnographic and natural sciences exhibited in the basic exhibitions or in the 72 objectives of the Ethnography Section. Museum of Natural Sciences Within it, visitors can admire 34 species of animals with over 230 specimens, from freshwater species to reptiles, various bird species or small mammals. Museum of History and Archeology The Department of History and Archeology includes four subsections: archeology, the Middle Ages and old, numismatic and modern and contemporary history. The Village Museum Established in 1977, primarily as a cultural necessity, but also for highlighting the ethnographic heritage of Vrancea, the museum is made up of 73 authentic constructions grouped in 32 complexes with over 6,000 different objects. Union Museum It is recognized that Focsani was a landmark in the unionist movement. The Union Museum presents a series of documents regarding this, together with a series of objects belonging to the family of Ruler Alexandru Ioan Cuza.
Public Garden It was inaugurated in 1873, on the site of the Gardens of St. John\s Monastery. It was until the Second World War one of the city\s landmarks. Nicolae Balcescu Park Built after 1950, on the land of a great Armenian landowner from the early twentieth century. Robert Schuman Park Robert Schuman, an eminent lawyer and French minister of foreign affairs during 1948 and 1952, is considered one of the founding fathers of the European Union. Heroes Mausoleum Park The park includes the Mausoleum of Heroes in Focsani is one of the four funerary monuments in the county raised in memory of the heroes fallen in World War I. Theater Park - Mr. Gh. Pastia Mr. Gh. Pastia Focsani Park is located in the immediate vicinity of Mr. Gh. Pastia Theater and is the ideal place to relax before a play.
Restaurant David\s For those who want to spend some pleasant moments with friends and children we have a generous terrace where you can serve the restaurant menu and an outdoor bar and for the little ones with a spacious playground and recreation area where they are supervised by a qualified staff. Casa Vranceana With a new design and a pleasant ambience, the Vrancea House is very close to the center of Focsani. The architecture, the furniture, the decorations, the terrace offered by the terrace and the kindness of the staff, all make you feel as good as home. Restaurant Laguna International restaurant. Restaurant Intim Intim restaurant is a wonderful retreat for those who want to give up (at least for a few hours) everyday routine, but also the right location for important events in your life. L\Atelier A pub for young people.
